            "title": "Barclays Upgrades Atlas Copco to Overweight and Significantly Raises Target Price",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>Barclays has upgraded its recommendation for Atlas Copco to \"overweight\" from \"equal weight\" and at the same time sharply increased its target price by 23 percent to 178 kronor from 145 kronor. This move prompted the stock to rise by more than 4 percent.</p><p>\n\nIn an analysis reviewed by Investing, the bank notes that organic sales growth has been virtually zero during 2024-2025--an unusual period in which the company has lagged behind both the sector and its largest European peers.</p><!-- Article --><p>\n\nFor 2026, medium single-digit growth is expected, mainly driven by Compressor Technique and Vacuum Technique, which together account for more than 70 percent of the group's EBIT.</p></div>",
